<font color="#FF0000">STARTING OVER</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep 18 19:19:37 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I learned ,for me, that it had nothing to do with what I did in country.  It was how I internalized it.  Guys with stong cultural, religious, and strong family background did better.  Having nothing to return home to equals two tours.  In the middle of counseling, my counselor told me that I should have never gone to Nam.  I was already f-u..  Dysfunctional family and all that.  Stil we went and we came home..most of us.. and tried to get on with our lives.<br>
Twenty years old, couldn't walk into a bar and buy a drink. <br>
Twenty<br>
Wound up in SoCal just to see if all those &quot;Beach Blanket Bingo&quot; movies were true.  Yup, they were!<br>
Thirty<br>
Establishing a career, raising a family. College student on the G.I.Bill.  No issues.<br>
Fourty<br>
Stop, look around! Where am I in life?  What's that shadow?  What do you mean you sleep all nite?  Do you really understand why I carry this .45 every where I go?  Yeah, I know I'm putting on weight.  So what if I weigh 450?  Ain't nobody going to mess with me.  I AM the biggest and baddest!<br>
Put that mirror here on the desk so I can sit here with my back to the door,hon.<br>
I guess I showed my manager and all the guys on my team that I don't take crap from anybody.  Besides, I wasn't really going to throw him through the window.<br>
Fouty-five<br>
Just what the hell do you mean &quot;Am I a Viet Nam Vet?&quot;  What the fuck does that have to do with anything?  Oh, sure you want me to go to the place called a Vet Center?  They going to put me in the VA Hospital?  FUCK YOU!!!!  There ain't nothing wrong with me!!  So what if the only time I feel good is when I eat?  I don't sit in my car and listen to the oldies station, I'm not burying food up in the hills, I don't even have a set of fatigues!<br>
O.K,O.K., I'll make the appointment.  You've been with me for twenty years and I'll do it for you.<br>
See, I don't have all those symptoms.  I don't have PTSD.  Well, all right I'll come. Tuesday nite , huh? Just vets, right?..........
